cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY

This paper is about assessing interdisciplinarity in bibliometric studies, which involves analyzing data from various fields and disciplines. The most relevant arXiv CS sub-category is likely cs.DL (Digital Libraries), which deals with the organization, management, and retrieval of digital information. Other relevant sub-categories include cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which focuses on searching and analyzing large collections of data, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which deals with the analysis of social networks and online communities, cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing), which involves the use of technology to analyze and create music, and cs.CY (Computers and Society), which examines the social and ethical implications of technology.
